    <stitle>ELECTRICAL SYSTEM TROUBLESHOOTING GUIDE - 9800 MODEL - LIGHT SYSTEMS - TROUBLESHOOTING - Headlights - 9800
        SBA
    </stitle>
    <svcman/>
    <svcproc svcproctype="troubleshoot" graphiccount="0">
        <title>Headlights - 9800 SBA</title>
        <table id="t0828010" tblwidth="full-page" frame="all" numbered="no" view="reveal">
            <title>Headlights - 9800 SBA</title>
            <tgroup cols="7" colsep="1" rowsep="1" align="center" charoff="50">
                <colspec colname="1" charoff="50" colwidth="0.59in"/>
                <colspec colname="2" charoff="50" colwidth="0.50in"/>
                <colspec colname="3" charoff="50" colwidth="1.82in"/>
                <colspec colname="4" charoff="50" colwidth="0.82in"/>
                <colspec colname="5" charoff="50" colwidth="0.74in"/>
                <colspec colname="6" charoff="50" colwidth="0.79in"/>
                <colspec colname="7" charoff="50" colwidth="1.44in"/>
                <thead>
                    <row>
                        <entry colname="1" rotate="0" align="center">
                            <para>
                                <emph type="bold">STEP</emph>
                            </para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="2" rotate="0" align="center">
                            <para>
                                <emph type="bold">KEY</emph>
                            </para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="3" rotate="0" align="center">
                            <para>
                                <emph type="bold">ACTION</emph>
                            </para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="4" rotate="0" align="center">
                            <para>
                                <emph type="bold">TEST POINTS</emph>
                            </para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="5" rotate="0" align="center">
                            <para>
                                <emph type="bold">SPEC.</emph>
                            </para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="6" rotate="0" align="center">
                            <para>
                                <emph type="bold">YES - IN SPEC.</emph>
                            </para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="7" rotate="0" align="center">
                            <para>
                                <emph type="bold">NO - OUT OF SPEC.</emph>
                            </para>
                        </entry>
                    </row>
                </thead>
                <tbody valign="top">
                    <row>
                        <entry rotate="0" align="center">
                            <para>1.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry rotate="0" align="center">
                            <para>Off</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry rotate="0">
                            <para>Does either headlight illuminate when headlight switch is moved to on position and the
                                dimmer switch is placed in low beam or high beam position?
                            </para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry rotate="0">
                            <para></para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry rotate="0">
                            <para></para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry rotate="0">
                            <para>Go to Step 10.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry rotate="0">
                            <para>Go to next step.</para>
                        </entry>
                    </row>
                    <row>
                        <entry rotate="0" align="center">
                            <para>2.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry rotate="0" align="center">
                            <para>Off</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry rotate="0">
                            <para>Remove 10A circuit breaker F6-C, and at circuit 14D, measure voltage to ground.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry rotate="0">
                            <para>F6-C, 14D to gnd.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry rotate="0">
                            <para>12 &#177; 1.5 volts.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry rotate="0">
                            <para>Go to next step.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry rotate="0">
                            <para>Locate cause of low or no voltage in circuit 14D from (B2) battery stud, then
                                repair.
                            </para>
                        </entry>
                    </row>
                    <row>
                        <entry rotate="0" align="center">
                            <para>3.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry rotate="0" align="center">
                            <para>Off</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry rotate="0">
                            <para>Disconnect headlight switch (410), re-install circuit breaker F6-C, and at circuit
                                50A, measure voltage to ground.
                            </para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry rotate="0">
                            <para>(410), 50A to gnd.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry rotate="0">
                            <para>12 &#177; 1.5 volts.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry rotate="0">
                            <para>Go to next step.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry rotate="0">
                            <para>Locate cause of low or no voltage in circuit breaker F6-C or circuit 50A, then
                                repair.
                            </para>
                        </entry>
                    </row>
                    <row>
                        <entry rotate="0" align="center">
                            <para>4.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry rotate="0" align="center">
                            <para>Off</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry rotate="0">
                            <para>Test headlight switch (410) by placing switch in headlight position and measuring
                                resistance from terminal 5 to 6.
                            </para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry rotate="0">
                            <para>(410), term. 5 to 6</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry rotate="0" align="center">
                            <para>&#60; 1 ohm.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry rotate="0" align="center">
                            <para>Go to next step.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry rotate="0">
                            <para>Replace defective switch</para>
                        </entry>
                    </row>
                    <row>
                        <entry rotate="0" align="center">
                            <para>5.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry rotate="0" align="center">
                            <para>Off</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry rotate="0">
                            <para>Remove headlight relay (462-R4) and reconnect headlight switch (410). Move headlight
                                switch to headlight position, and at relay socket (462-R4) and circuit 50B, measure
                                voltage to ground.
                            </para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry rotate="0">
                            <para>(462- R4), 50B to gnd.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry rotate="0">
                            <para>12 &#177; 1.5 volts.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry rotate="0">
                            <para>Go to next step.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry rotate="0">
                            <para>Locate cause of low or no voltage in circuit 50B, then repair.</para>
                        </entry>
                    </row>
                    <row>
                        <entry rotate="0" align="center">
                            <para>6.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry rotate="0" align="center">
                            <para>Off</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry rotate="0">
                            <para>At relay socket (462-R4) and circuit 51, measure voltage to ground.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry rotate="0">
                            <para>(462- R4), 51 to gnd.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry rotate="0">
                            <para>12 &#177; 1.5 volts.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry rotate="0">
                            <para>Go to next step.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry rotate="0">
                            <para>Locate cause of low or no voltage in 20A circuit breaker or circuit 51, then repair.
                            </para>
                        </entry>
                    </row>
                    <row>
                        <entry rotate="0" align="center">
                            <para>7.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry rotate="0" align="center">
                            <para>Off</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry rotate="0">
                            <para>At relay socket (462-R4), measure voltage from circuit 51 to 50-GB.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry rotate="0">
                            <para>(462- R4), 51 to 50-GB.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry rotate="0">
                            <para>12 &#177; 1.5 volts.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry rotate="0">
                            <para>Go to next step.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry rotate="0">
                            <para>Locate open or poor connection in cir. 50-GB, 75-GC, 75-GB, 11-GN, or 11-GB to right
                                cab ground stud (404), then repair.
                            </para>
                        </entry>
                    </row>
                    <row>
                        <entry rotate="0" align="center">
                            <para>8.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry rotate="0" align="center">
                            <para>Off</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry rotate="0">
                            <para>Bench test headlight relay (462-R4) by measuring resistance from terminal 30 to 87A.
                            </para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry rotate="0">
                            <para>Relay (462- R4), term. 30 to 87A.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry rotate="0" align="center">
                            <para>&#60; 1 ohm.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry rotate="0">
                            <para>Go to next step.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry rotate="0">
                            <para>Replace defective headlight relay.</para>
                        </entry>
                    </row>
                    <row>
                        <entry rotate="0" align="center">
                            <para>9.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry rotate="0" align="center">
                            <para>Off</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry rotate="0">
                            <para>Bench test headlight relay (462-R4) by applying +12 volts to terminal 86, ground to
                                terminal 85, and measuring resistance from terminal 30 to 87.
                            </para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry rotate="0">
                            <para>Energized relay (462- R4), term. 30 to 87.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry rotate="0">
                            <para>&#60; 1 ohm.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry rotate="0">
                            <para>Go to next step.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry rotate="0">
                            <para>Replace defective headlight relay.</para>
                        </entry>
                    </row>
                    <row>
                        <entry rotate="0" align="center">
                            <para>10.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry rotate="0" align="center">
                            <para>Off</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry rotate="0">
                            <para>Disconnect dimmer switch (70) and re-install headlight relay (462-R4). Move headlight
                                switch to on position and at connector (70) and circuit 51A, measure voltage to ground.
                            </para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry rotate="0">
                            <para>(70), 51A to gnd.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry rotate="0">
                            <para>12 &#177; 1.5 volts.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry rotate="0">
                            <para>Go to next step.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry rotate="0">
                            <para>Locate cause of low or no voltage in circuit 51A, then repair.</para>
                        </entry>
                    </row>
                    <row>
                        <entry rotate="0" align="center">
                            <para>11.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry rotate="0" align="center">
                            <para>Off</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry rotate="0">
                            <para>Test dimmer switch (70) by placing it in low beam position and measuring resistance
                                from terminal B to C.
                            </para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry rotate="0">
                            <para>Sw. (70), term. B to C.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry rotate="0" align="center">
                            <para>&#60; 1 ohm.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry rotate="0">
                            <para>Go to next step.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry rotate="0">
                            <para>Replace defective switch.</para>
                        </entry>
                    </row>
                    <row>
                        <entry rotate="0" align="center">
                            <para>12.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry rotate="0" align="center">
                            <para>Off</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry rotate="0">
                            <para>Test dimmer switch (70) by placing it in high beam position and measuring resistance
                                from terminal B to A.
                            </para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry rotate="0">
                            <para>Sw. (70), term. B to A.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry rotate="0">
                            <para>&#60; 1 ohm.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry rotate="0">
                            <para>Go to next step.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry rotate="0">
                            <para>Replace defective switch.</para>
                        </entry>
                    </row>
                    <row>
                        <entry rotate="0" align="center">
                            <para>13.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry rotate="0" align="center">
                            <para>Off</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry rotate="0">
                            <para>Disconnect right headlight connector (2), move headlight switch to on position, and
                                dimmer switch to low beam position. At conn. (2) and red wire, measure voltage to
                                ground.
                            </para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry rotate="0">
                            <para>(2), red wire to gnd.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry rotate="0" align="center">
                            <para>12 &#177; 1.5 volts.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry rotate="0">
                            <para>Go to next step.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry rotate="0">
                            <para>Locate cause of low or no voltage in circuit 53, 53A, conn. (400)/(498), cir. 53A,
                                conn. (243), or red wire, then repair.
                            </para>
                        </entry>
                    </row>
                    <row>
                        <entry rotate="0" align="center">
                            <para>14.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry rotate="0" align="center">
                            <para>Off</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry rotate="0">
                            <para>With switches still set, at connector (2), measure voltage from red wire to blue
                                wire.
                            </para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry rotate="0">
                            <para>(2), red wire to blue wire.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry rotate="0" align="center">
                            <para>12 &#177; 1.5 volts.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry rotate="0">
                            <para>Go to next step.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry rotate="0">
                            <para>Locate open or poor connection in blue wire, conn. (243), cir. 50-GA, 11-GK, conn.
                                (400)/(498), cir. 11-GK or 11-G to right cab ground stud (404), then repair.
                            </para>
                        </entry>
                    </row>
                    <row>
                        <entry rotate="0" align="center">
                            <para>15.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry rotate="0" align="center">
                            <para>Off</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry rotate="0">
                            <para>With switches still set, reconnect connector (2). Does right headlight illuminate?
                            </para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry rotate="0">
                            <para></para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry rotate="0">
                            <para></para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry rotate="0">
                            <para>Go to next step.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry rotate="0">
                            <para>Replace defective lamp.</para>
                        </entry>
                    </row>
                    <row>
                        <entry rotate="0" align="center">
                            <para>16.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry rotate="0" align="center">
                            <para>Off</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry rotate="0">
                            <para>Disconnect left headlight connector (2), move headlight switch to on position, and
                                dimmer switch to low beam position. At connector (2) and red wire, measure voltage to
                                ground.
                            </para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry rotate="0">
                            <para>(2), red wire to gnd.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry rotate="0">
                            <para>12 &#177; 1.5 volts.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry rotate="0">
                            <para>Go to next step.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry rotate="0">
                            <para>Locate cause of low or no voltage in circuit 53B, conn. (423)/(498), cir. 53B, conn.
                                (243), or red wire, then repair.
                            </para>
                        </entry>
                    </row>
                    <row>
                        <entry rotate="0" align="center">
                            <para>17.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry rotate="0" align="center">
                            <para>Off</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry rotate="0">
                            <para>With switches still set, at connector (2), measure voltage from red wire to blue
                                wire.
                            </para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry rotate="0">
                            <para>(2), red wire to blue wire.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry rotate="0">
                            <para>12 &#177; 1.5 volts.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry rotate="0">
                            <para>Go to next step.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry rotate="0">
                            <para>Locate open or poor connection in blue wire, conn. (243), cir. 50-G, 11-GL, conn.
                                (423)/(498), cir. 11-GL, conn. (490), cir. 11-GM or 11-GF to left cab ground stud (429),
                                then repair. [With Canadian DRL ground path from conn. (490) is through cir. 66J, relay
                                (475) N.C. contacts, and cir. 66-GA to G6 gnd. adapter (616)]
                            </para>
                        </entry>
                    </row>
                    <row>
                        <entry rotate="0" align="center">
                            <para>18.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry rotate="0" align="center">
                            <para>Off</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry rotate="0">
                            <para>With switches still set, reconnect connector (2). Does left headlight illuminate?
                            </para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry rotate="0" align="center">
                            <para></para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry rotate="0" align="center">
                            <para></para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry rotate="0">
                            <para>Go to next step.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry rotate="0">
                            <para>Replace defective lamp.</para>
                        </entry>
                    </row>
                    <row>
                        <entry rotate="0" align="center">
                            <para>19.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry rotate="0" align="center">
                            <para>Off</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry rotate="0">
                            <para>Disconnect right headlight connector (2), move headlight switch to on position, and
                                dimmer switch to high beam position. At conn. (2) and brown wire, measure voltage to
                                ground.
                            </para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry rotate="0">
                            <para>(2), brown wire to gnd.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry rotate="0">
                            <para>12 &#177; 1.5 volts.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry rotate="0">
                            <para>Go to next step.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry rotate="0">
                            <para>Locate cause of low or no voltage in circuit 52 or 52B, conn. (400)/(498), cir. 52B,
                                conn. (243), or brown wire, then repair.
                            </para>
                        </entry>
                    </row>
                    <row>
                        <entry rotate="0" align="center">
                            <para>20.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry rotate="0" align="center">
                            <para>Off</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry rotate="0">
                            <para>With switches still set, reconnect connector (2). Does right headlight illuminate?
                            </para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry rotate="0">
                            <para></para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry rotate="0">
                            <para></para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry rotate="0">
                            <para>Go to next step.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry rotate="0">
                            <para>Replace defective lamp.</para>
                        </entry>
                    </row>
                    <row>
                        <entry rotate="0" align="center">
                            <para>21.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry rotate="0" align="center">
                            <para>Off</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry rotate="0">
                            <para>Disconnect left headlight connector (2), move headlight switch to on position, and
                                dimmer switch to high beam position. At connector (2) and brown wire, measure voltage to
                                ground.
                            </para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry rotate="0">
                            <para>(2), brown wire to gnd.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry rotate="0" align="center">
                            <para>12 &#177; 1.5 volts.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry rotate="0">
                            <para>Go to next step.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry rotate="0">
                            <para>Locate cause of low or no voltage in cir. 52C, conn. (423)/(498), cir. 52C, conn.
                                (243), or brown wire, then repair.
                            </para>
                        </entry>
                    </row>
                    <row>
                        <entry rotate="0" align="center">
                            <para>22.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry rotate="0" align="center">
                            <para>Off</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry rotate="0">
                            <para>With switches still set, reconnect conn. (2). Does left headlight illuminate?</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry rotate="0" align="center">
                            <para></para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry rotate="0" align="center">
                            <para></para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry rotate="0">
                            <para>Head- light cir. check good.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry rotate="0">
                            <para>Replace defective lamp.</para>
                        </entry>
                    </row>
                </tbody>
            </tgroup>
        </table>
